                    </div>
                    <span>This is one of the few O'Reilly books that I read cover to cover.  What?  A book on regular expressions read cover to cover?  If you have read the book, I suspect that you understand.  If not, read it.  Even a cursory skimming (if possible) will provide valuable information in HOW regular expressions work - the syntax, the underlying engine, differences in implementation.  Highly recommended.  
<br />
<br />On a sidenote, the regular expression in the back of the book (a full page long) has been the topic of conversation in my workplace more than once.  I suspect that it will eventually become one of those "geek indicators" like the number 42 or PARC.</span>
                  
